INSERT INTO `#__ak_storage`  VALUES ('liveupdate', '2015-12-18 13:31:54', '{\"stuck\":0,\"software\":\"Akeeba Backup for WordPress\",\"version\":\"1.6.0\",\"link\":\"http:\\/\\/cdn.akeebabackup.com\\/downloads\\/backupwp\\/1.6.0\\/akeebabackupwp-core.zip\",\"date\":\"2015-12-18\",\"releasenotes\":\"<h3>Release highlights<\\/h3><p>    <strong>IMPORTANT! Behaviour change.<\\/strong> All remote backup features (front-end URL, JSON API) will be    automatically <em>disabled<\\/em> if you are using a Secret Word that\'s not strong enough. This is done to protect    your against brute forcing of the Secret Word which could allow attackers to take and download backups of your    sites. Please read our release announcement for more information.<\\/p><p>    <strong>Text log in ALICE, the log analyzer<\\/strong>. You can paste that text when you are requesting support to    help us help you more efficiently.<\\/p><p>    <strong>Automatically run ALICE if an error occurs<\\/strong> (only applies to backups taken from the interactive web    interface).<\\/p><p>    <strong>Added support for Magento 2 and Drupal 8<\\/strong> (Akeeba Solo only).<\\/p><p>    <strong>Support for Amazon S3\'s Standard- Infrequent Access storage type<\\/strong> (Professional versions only)<\\/p><p>    <strong>More stable Site Transfer Wizard<\\/strong> thanks to improved transfer chunk size calculations<\\/p><p>    <strong>Security update (very low importance issue)<\\/strong>. Someone who already knows your Secret Word can store    XSS in the database if the remote backup is enabled and you\'re not using the security enhanced .htaccess file    (discovered by NCC Group). Low importance because this security issue requires the attacker to already know your    Secret Word. However, if they have it they can already take and download backups of your site, exposing you to much    higher and immediate risk. Therefore we consider it a low importance issue: it requires your site to essentially    be already compromised.<\\/p><h3>Core and Professional versions<\\/h3><p>    Now all of our backup software (Akeeba Backup for Joomla! and    WordPress, as well as Akeeba Solo) come in two editions: Core and Professional. The Core version is provided free    of charge to everybody <em>WITHOUT having to subscribe, register or login<\\/em> and contains roughly 80% of the    features. The Professional version is only available to paid subscribers \\u2013depending on their subscription level\\u2013    and contains all the features. Support is only provided for the Professional version to eligible subscribers.<\\/p><p>    We strongly recommend installing and using the Core version before purchasing the Professional version. There are    no refunds given on grounds of server compatibility, usability or software capabilities since these can be easily    determined by installing the Core version on your server and\\/or reading our documentation, both available free of    charge to everybody. If you have a question regarding our software please use the Contact Us link to submit a    pre-sales request. Our staff will be most happy to respond to your requests!<\\/p><h3>PHP 5.3.3 or later or PHP 7 is required<\\/h3><p>    Good news, folks! We listened to your feedback and restored compatibility with all versions of    PHP from 5.3.04 onwards, including 5.4, 5.5, 5.6 and the just-released 7.0.    We\'d like to remind you that most third party software which can be    backed up by our software do not necessarily support PHP 7. As a result we can\'t guarantee the trouble-free    operation of the restoration procedure or the restored site if you are using PHP 7.<\\/p><p>    <small>Note: there is no such thing as PHP 6. PHP versions jumped from 5.6 to 7.0. Why? Well,        <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/philsturgeon.uk\\/php\\/2014\\/07\\/23\\/neverending-muppet-debate-of-php-6-v-php-7\\/\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">it\'s a long story<\\/a>. TL;DR: It doesn\'t have to make sense, just accept it.    <\\/small><\\/p><h3>Changelog<\\/h3><h4>Bug fixes<\\/h4><ul>\\t<li>[HIGH] Could not save configuration without enabling the One-click backup icon<\\/li>\\t<li>[HIGH] Drupal: Fixed endless loop while trying to read the configuration<\\/li>\\t<li>[LOW] Added workaround for untranslated text caused by disabled parse_ini_* functions<\\/li>\\t<li>[LOW] Fixed PhpBB platform recognition<\\/li>\\t<li>[LOW] Fixed typo in ALICE<\\/li>\\t<li>[LOW] No Status displayed in the Latest Backup module for successful backups<\\/li>\\t<li>[LOW] Site Transfer Wizard, bad performance of the test FTP\\/SFTP servers could lead to an instant error when accessing this feature<\\/li>\\t<li>[LOW] Someone who already knows your Secret Word can store XSS in the database if the remote backup is enabled and you\'re not using the security enhanced .htaccess file (discovered by NCC Group)<\\/li>\\t<li>[LOW] The Configuration Wizard would fail to correctly detect configuration settings of Joomla! sites whose configuration.php file contains comments (e.g. using a copy of the configuration.php-dist file)<\\/li>\\t<li>[MEDIUM] Fixed routing issue in Site Transfer Wizard<\\/li>\\t<li>[MEDIUM] One Click Backup buttons wouldn\'t actually switch the backup profile<\\/li>\\t<li>[MEDIUM] The \\\"Include Akeeba Solo in the backup\\\" feature would cause restoration issues<\\/li><\\/ul><h4>New features<\\/h4><ul>\\t<li>Added support for Magento 2<\\/li>\\t<li>Added textual output to ALICE so it could be included in support tickets<\\/li>\\t<li>Automatically run ALICE if an error occurs during the last domain of a backup<\\/li>\\t<li>Support for Amazon S3\'s Standard- Infrequent Access storage type<\\/li><\\/ul><h4>Miscellaneous changes<\\/h4><ul>\\t<li>More stable Site Transfer Wizard thanks to improved transfer chunk size calculations<\\/li><\\/ul><h4>Critical bugs and important changes<\\/h4><ul>\\t<li>Front-end and remote backup features will be DISABLED if we detect an insecure Secret Word<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"infourl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.akeebabackup.com\\/download\\/backupwp\\/1-6-0.html\",\"md5\":\"6f9511a25615929e7692206f2c893933\",\"sha1\":\"d1286cf52b213269da7e9d5db913f253f77e7f76\",\"platforms\":\"wordpress\\/3.8+,php\\/5.3,php\\/5.4,php\\/5.5,php\\/5.6,php\\/7.0\"}'), ('liveupdate_lastcheck', '2015-12-18 13:31:54', '1450441914');
